This paper deals with natural language generation from structured data, specifically Abstract Meaning Representations (AMRs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to train models for generating sentences, which suggests categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization algorithms for approximating the best sequence of actions, which could fall under categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
